annotation.TEXT: Oh, and don't worry, I'm not going to take that pipe leading to the world 1 warp again!
Huh. I'm surprised that I can't scroll the screen backwards from here.
Should I mention that little text quirk on the Exploding Rabbit forums? Let me know, guys!

Alright, so you saw there how the parakoopa gave me 400 when I removed its wings (which is correct), but then it gave me 400 (instead of the 100 I should've gotten) when I stomped it again to make it hide in its shell. I could've sworn that the parakoopa scoring issue was fixed in the past, but I guess not quite.
Alright, I guess I'll clean out this bonus room again.
Well, I'm now using the Symphony of the Night Trevor?!
Okay, with that first power up, Trevor?'s whip is strengthened.
Cool, I got the Wave Beam! I really like having this weapon for Samus in SMB Crossover.
Fortunately, Samus was just fast enough to get to the right side of the moving platform in time anyway.
Shut up, clock.
Forget those two coins I skipped! (Actually, I probably did have enough time to grab them.)
However, not only that, but you can enter this pipe over here as well, which leads to another section of 1-2 that I didn't show at all last time.

Oh, yeah. I never showed you guys this small section in between the bonus room's entrance and exit last time I was here. (And I really should've come here last time, since Dark Link could've benefitted from the power up here.)
Yeah, I think I'm doing well enough on time to stop and empty this multi-coin block.
Hah. With certain characters' weapons, you can access this vine from the "wrong" side.
Of course, hitting the block they're standing on works too. Also, there's a star there (which looks like a triforce in this case). Oh, and I picked up some missiles. Nice.
Well, I did get 2950 more time bonus points than if I'd finished with 36 seconds left, and the fireworks I missed were worth 3000, so I guess that's nearly perfectly fair.
Okay, now for 1-2, I'm going to go with the Tetris-mobile!
D'oh. I missed a couple. I was hoping to get a perfect this time...
Oh, Varia! Now Samus is protected from fire bars! (Might be handy not only in the castle levels, but also in certain other levels that contain fire bars in The Lost Levels.)
Star power, activate!
Ooh, the "Wall 1" ability. Now I just need "Wall 2" (for ceilings), and Sophia III will be fully upgraded.
Oh, noes. I left one rupee behind. Now everyone's OCDs will go nuts.

So, Twitch managed to defeat Champion Iris in Blaze Black 2 earlier today, and they also managed to capture Dialga with a single Dusk Ball. They also caught a couple of Zekroms as well (the first one being a guaranteed shiny). That's pretty awesome.
Alright, looks like Trevor? wants to go through the sky bonus area.
Ooh, 3-way missiles! Those are capable of defeating Buzzy Beetles and Bullet Bills!
...Wait, what? 400, 400, 500? Shouldn't I have gotten 400, 100, 500 for stomping that parakoopa like that? Umm... I'll double-check this with another parakoopa later in the level.
Alt. skin votes include: 1 vote for Tetromino (Sophia III), 1 vote for Zero Suit Samus, 1 vote for a random Luigi skin, 1 vote for SMB Luigi, and 1 vote for a random Simon skin.
Oh, well. It doesn't matter anyway, because... That's right! I'm totally heading all the way back to world 1!
Yep, I'm running out of time, but hopefully I have enough left to do one last thing way back here...
Oh, neat. The fire flower becomes a candle with the Zelda II graphics.
Oh, man. Hammer brothers. Good thing I can just shoot them.
Gotcha! I figured I'd be able to grab that 1-up, since I believe it stops moving but doesn't actually despawn while it's off screen.
Instead, I'm going to go down this pipe over here! (Yep, I'm going this way, folks.)
Sure, I'll grab that missile. Oh, it looks like these bricks over this pit contain coins now (probably so that you don't end up in an unwinnable situation if you're going nuts with your weapons).
Blaster combo! (9 hits) 2-life combo!

Yep! (That would've been silly if I fell straight down the pit in front of the flagpole.) Okay, so I believe if I keep going, I should eventually reach the world 1 warp zone, but I have so little time left...
Alright, quickly hit this brick over here to reveal a vine and then climb up it!
Okay, so I didn't travel over here last time, but I'm doing so now to show you that the warp zone to world 2 is over here.
Gimme that mushroom! I need to power up my weapon so that I can break bricks with one hit.
Finally killed one of them, and I could really use that big heart.
There's that "green orb with a plus" 1-up. (Sorry I didn't let it fully emerge before grabbing it, but you guys probably saw enough of it.)
Yeah, tear down that wall!
Now, Trevor? can't jump very high, but he's capable of double-jumping, which more than makes up for that.
Cool, I got homing missiles. Now can I get some 3-way missiles?
Alright, now let's see if Luigi can do what Dark Link was too slow to do here a couple episodes ago...
Whoops, I didn't intend to climb the wall there.
Also, Trevor? starts with throwing knives and 15 hearts to use them with, and I'm going to use them right now to combat these Gumas with.
To be continued... Yo!
And there's the warp to world 4. However, I'm not going to use that warp zone.
Yeah, get outta here, poison mushroom.
And, here's the warp to world 3, which I will use to return to 3-1!
...Really? I managed to miss the 6 there?
SPRING!!! Can I go over the flagpole with this?
Alright, I'm going to start things off today with Zero Suit Samus.
Oh, yeah. Now that I've grabbed a mushroom (heart container in this case), my beam's range has increased.

I don't really consider this cheating, since I went over the flagpole with about 40 seconds left on the clock, so I probably would've cleared with 36 left (for the 6 fireworks) if I wasn't interested in checking this one thing.
Sweet! ...But, can I maybe include that parakoopa in the combo as well?
Alright, sky bonus time!
Nuts, didn't quite get it. Also, if a kicked shell goes too far off screen in SMB Crossover, it despawns and is considered dead (it won't respawn if I go back to its original location).
I believe the game gave me the SMW Luigi skin.
I'm just going over the top of most of this area since I don't want to waste time.
Oh, man. If that cannon had fired a Moa at the wrong time there, I might've been in trouble.
Umm... You know what? This is gonna bother me if I don't check it, so I'm actually going to turn on the infinite time cheat, just to see if the warp to world 1 is indeed over to the right.
Alright, now since Luigi's number 1, I think I'll have him play 1-1 here! I'll go with a random Luigi skin.
I'll take that invincibility star, thank you very much.
Hitting those coin blocks is easy with bombs. Whoa! I thought I was gonna fall in that pit because I failed to jump properly there!
Hah! Take that, wall!
Alright, the infinite time cheat is disabled, which sets my time limit to 100 if it was lower than that.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Up above are the voting results this time.
Alright, got the Crusher and Hover power ups here.
Now this is how you'd normally access the vine. However, I'm not gonna have Samus climb up the vine again.
I like how the poison mushroom is a red orb with a minus sign in it with the Blaster Master graphics. (I believe the 1-up is a green orb with a plus sign in it.)
Umm... What's with the text right here? The "C" is like mashed into the end of "press" here.
Fortunately, it's safe to consume a vial of poison while invincible.
Bah, missed one of the last three. But, I also missed one other coin in that area, so it wouldn't have been a perfect anyway. Alright, now to go back to the left for stuff...
There's a hidden 1-up that would be extremely difficult for Mario to collect, but most other characters (including Samus) have no problem getting it.
Okay, there's not much time left! Hurry!
And with that power up, Trevor?'s whip becomes longer.
Heck, yeah. Goin' down a pipe.
D'oh... Well, that's alright. I should be able to eventually catch up with that 1-up.
Awesome. More hearts.
Alright, I'm glad I had enough time to do all that! Now, for my second visit to 3-1, I'm going to go with a random Simon skin, since he's the only character I haven't used in The Lost Levels yet.
...What? How did I just miss the 6 there? Argh...
...Um... Uh, oh. Am I stuck here? Actually, no, thanks to this holy water... assuming I can aim it right...
I thought about shortcutting to the vine again here (which Trevor? can certainly do using his whip), but I changed my mind.
...It's this bonus room with the bullet cannon again. (Aw, I should've shown off the 3-way missiles against the Bullet Bills here...)
Bah, I don't want to waste time with this parakoopa. There's a lot of stuff I want to do in 1-2 this time, and I don't know if I'll have enough time on the time limit to do it all...
Yeah, I decided to fall there on purpose. I don't want to risk running out of time.
What the heck? That's cheap! I was so on the right side of that moving platform!
Yeah, yeah. Samus can shoot upwards, go into morph ball mode, and place bombs.
There's a multi-coin block that I'll quickly clean out here.
Alright, everybody's been used at least once in The Lost Levels now, so vote for whoever you want me to use next time! (Note: 3-2 is a water level.)

However, I'm allowed to go back to the flagpole in this case. I'm guessing that going to the warp zone through 3-1's first bonus room actually sends you to a completely different map in SMB Crossover, which consists of only the warp zone area, so that's why I couldn't go left to the flagpole from there.
And once again I leave behind a coin to mess with everyone's OCDs. Alright, so after going through that bonus room, I end up back in the main area of 1-2. Now, let's backtrack!
Oh, come on. Don't fumble with the Hover now!
Yeah, yeah. I know I'm running low on time, but I'm not worried. Now, obviously, watch out for the bullet cannon in this room.
Whoa, man. That could've gotten a bit dicey there.
Okay, the world 1 warp zone is indeed accessible this way as well.
Now, if you go down this pipe...
There we go! (However, I checked this later, and I wouldn't have been stuck anyway. The pipe I just came out of can be reentered, and it takes me to that pipe just to my right. So, that's good.)
Hmm... NES? Or SNES? ...I'll go with the NES one.
